This paper discusses the use of linguistic typology in natural language processing, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in utilizing typological information. Additionally, the paper discusses information retrieval (cs.IR) and cross-lingual NLP (cs.CY), which are both relevant to the use of typological information in NLP.
